title: Whale, dugong and turtle populations still reeling from past fishing practices
text:
Topix › Pacific Travel › Whale, dugong and turtle populations ... Whale, dugong and turtle populations still reeling from past fishing practices Next Story Prev Story 5 hrs ago Read more: ABC News 
Can you imagine riding a turtle or fishing for dugongs? These actions sound unthinkable but they were both once considered completely acceptable in the Great Barrier Reef. Mark Read from the Great Barrier Reef Marine Park Authority says these practices are still affecting species today, even though they've been outlawed for decades.   ABC News.
